uare.svg}}   <!--Middle'bgh name marker-->\n{{Location map~|North Yorkshire        |label   = '''[[Harrogate]]'''        | lat= 53.991| long=-1.539|position=left|background =yellow}}\n{{Location map~|North Yorkshire        |label   = [[Scarborough, North Yorkshire|Scarborough]]     |lat= 54.2773\n|long = -0.4017|position=left        |background =yellow}}\n{{Location map~|North Yorkshire        |label   = [[Redcar]] |lat=54.61856|long= -1.06856|position=right|background =yellow}}\n{{Location map~|North Yorkshire        |label   = [[Thornaby-on-Tees]]      |lat=54.5556|long=-1.3049 |background =white |label_width=19    |position=left}}\n{{Location map~|North Yorkshire        |label   = [[Ingleby Barwick]]  |lat=54.519|long=-1.311  |background =white  |label_width=19|position=right}}\n{{Location map~|North Yorkshire        |label   = [[Yarm]] |lat=54.505|long=-1.348 |position = bottom        |background =white}}\n{{Location map~|North Yorkshire        |label   = [[Selby]]   |lat=53.781789 |long= -1.070309 |position=right        |background =yellow}}      {{Location map~|North Yorkshire        |label   = [[Guisborough]]   |lat= 54.555|long=-1.0563     |position=right|background =white      }}\n {{Location map~|North Yorkshire        |label   = '''[[Northallerton]]'''    |lat= 54.3378|long=-1.4285  |position= right   |label_size=105|background =yellow}}\n{{Location map~|North Yorkshire        |label   = '''[[Ripon]]'''   | lat=54.13796 | long=-1.52365|position = left||label_size=105|background =white}}\n{{Location map~|North Yorkshire        |label   = [[Knaresborough]]  |long=-1.467|lat=54.0084\n |position = top|background =white}}\n{{Location map~|North Yorkshire        |label   = [[Skipton]]     | lat= 53.962 | long=-2.017 |position = left|background =yellow}}\n{{Location map~|North Yorkshire        |label   = [[Whitby]]     |lat= 54.4858|long= -0.6206 |position = left|background =white}}\n{{Location map~|North Yorkshire        |label   = [[Richmond, North Yorkshire|Richmond]]   | lat=  54.403\n| long=-1.737 |position = left|background =yellow}}\n{{Location map~|North Yorkshire        |label   = {{bg|white|[[Norton-on-Derwent]]}} | lat= 54.132\n| long= -0.783 |position = right}}\n{{Location map~|North Yorkshire        |label   = [[Pickering, North Yorkshire|Pickering]] | lat=  54.2439\n| long=-0.7760 |position = left|background =white}}\n{{Location map~|North Yorkshire        |label   = [[Tadcaster]]  | lat=   53.8852\n| long= -1.2620|position = left|background =white}}\n{{Location map~|North Yorkshire        |label   = [[Malton, North Yorkshire|Malton]]  ||lat = 54.139\n|long = -0.792|position = left|background =yellow}}\n}}\n\n===Settlements by district population===\n\n''Settlements in italics lie only within the ceremonial county, not the administrative county.''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Rank\n! Town\n! Population<br>(2011)\n! Borough\n! Definition\n! Notes\n|-\n| 1\n| ''[[York]]''\n| 152,841<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E35000051 |title=York (Built-up area subdivision) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| City of York\n| City\n| Refers to the built-up area subdivision, which excludes any outlying areas from the city's boundaries. The City of York borough covers a wider area than York itself, encompassing surrounding towns and villages.\n|-\n| 2\n| ''[[Middlesbrough]]''\n|  138,142<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E06000002/ |title=Middlesbrough (Local authority) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| Middlesbrough\n| Town\n| Refers to the measurement of the Middlesbrough local authority at the 2011 census. This is accurate to the town's boundaries, not including any outlying areas which fall under [[Middlesbrough Council]]. \n|-\n| 3\n| [[Harrogate]]\n| 73,576<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E35000975 |title=Harrogate (Built-up area subdivision) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| Harrogate\n| Town\n| Unparished, but the built-up area subdivision accurately corresponds to the town's boundaries, with no outlying areas.\n|-\n| 4\n| [[Scarborough, North Yorkshire|Scarborough]]\n| 38,715 (approximate)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E34004408 |title=Scarborough (Built-up area) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E04007709 |title=Eastfield (Parish) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E04007694 |title=Osgodby (Parish) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E04007663 |title=Cayton (Parish) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E04007691 |title=Newby and Scalby (Parish) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E04007697 |title=Seamer (Parish) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| Scarborough\n| Town\n| Town is unparished. There was no population count measuring Scarborough independently at the 2011 census. The built-up area is the closest, but also includes the outlying parishes of Eastfield, Osgodby, Cayton, Newby and Scalby, and part of Seamer. Subtracting the populations of all these parishes from the built-up area count of 61,749, comes to 38,715.\n|-\n| 5\n| ''[[Redcar]]''\n| 37,073<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E35000002 |title=Redcar (Built-up area subdivision) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| Redcar and Cleveland\n| Town\n| Unparished, but the built-up area subdivision accurately corresponds to the town's boundaries, with no outlying areas.\n|-\n| 6\n| ''[[Thornaby-on-Tees]]''\n| 24,741<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E35001481 |title=Thornaby-on-Tees (Built-up area subdivision) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| Stockton-on-Tees (South)\n| Town\n| Unitary Authority. The built-up area subdivision accurately corresponds to the town's boundaries, with no outlying areas.\n|-\n| 7\n| ''[[Ingleby Barwick]]''\n| 20,378<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E04000275 |title=Ingleby Barwick (Parish) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| Stockton-on-Tees (South)\n| Civil Parish\n|\n|-\n| 8\n| ''[[Saltburn, Marske and New Marske]]''\n| 19,134<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E04000266 |title=Saltburn, Marske and New Marske (Parish) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| Redcar & Cleveland\n| Civil Parish\n|\n|-\n| 9\n| ''[[Guisborough]]''\n| 17,777<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E04000263 |title=Guisborough (Parish) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| Redcar & Cleveland\n| Civil Parish\n| \n|-\n| 10\n| [[Ripon]]\n| 16,702<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E04007409 |title=Ripon (Parish) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| Harrogate\n| Civil Parish\n| City\n|-\n| 11\n| [[Knaresborough]]\n| 15,441<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E04007372 |title=Knaresborough (Parish) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| Harrogate\n| Civil Parish\n|\n|-\n| 12\n| [[Selby]]\n| 14,731<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E04007765 |title=Selby (Parish) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| Selby\n| Civil Parish\n|\n|-\n| 13\n| [[Skipton]]\n| 14,623<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E04007117 |title=Skipton (Parish) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| Craven\n| Civil Parish\n|\n|-\n| 14\n| [[Whitby]]\n| 13,213<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E04007706 |title=Whitby (Parish) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| Scarborough\n| Civil Parish\n|\n|-\n| 15\n| ''[[Skelton and Brotton]]''\n| 12,848<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E04000267 |title=Skelton and Brotton (Parish) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| Redcar & Cleveland\n| Civil Parish\n| \n|-\n| 16\n| [[Northallerton]]\n| 10,655<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E04007234 |title=Northallerton (Parish) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| Hambleton\n| Civil Parish\n| County town\n|-\n| 17\n| [[Haxby]]\n| 8,428<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E04000603 |title=Haxby (Parish) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| City of York\n| Civil Parish\n|\n|-\n| 18\n| [[Richmond, North Yorkshire|Richmond]]\n| 8,413<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E04007520 |title=Richmond (Parish) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| Richmondshire\n| Civil Parish\n|\n|-\n| 19\n| ''[[Yarm-on-Tees]]''\n| 8,384<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E04012074 |title=Yarm (Parish) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| Stockton-on-Tees (South)\n| Civil Parish\n| \n|-\n| 20\n| ''[[Loftus, North Yorkshire|Loftus]]''\n| 7,988<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/reports/localarea?compare=E04000265 |title=Loftus (Parish) |publisher=Official Labour Market Statistics |accessdate=23 February 2020  }}</ref>\n| Redcar & Cleveland\n| Civil Parish\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n=== List of settlements ===\n{{see also|List of civil parishes in North Yorkshire}}\n[[File:HolyTrinity back 8812.jpg|thumb|Holy Trinity, Wensley, a 13th-century church built on eighth-century foundations]]\n''Settlements in italics lie only within the ceremonial county, not the administrative county.''\n[[File:Yarm-bridge-viaduct02.jpg|thumb|[[Yarm]] bridge and Viaduct ]]\n\n* ''[[Acomb, North Yorkshire|Acomb]]'', [[Alne, North Yorkshire|Alne]], [[Ampleforth]], [[Appleton-le-Moors]]\n* [[Bedale]], ''[[Bishopthorpe]]'', [[Bolton-on-Swale]], [[Boroughbridge]], [[Borrowby, Hambleton|Borrowby (Hambleton)]], [[Borrowby, Scarborough|Borrowby (Scarborough)]], [[Brompton, Hambleton|Brompton (Hambleton)]], ''[[Brotton]]'', [[Buckden, North Yorkshire|Buckden]]\n* [[Castleton, North Yorkshire|Castleton]], [[Catterick, North Yorkshire|Catterick]], [[Catterick Garrison]], [[Cawood]], [[Clapham, North Yorkshire|Clapham]], [[Conistone]], ''[[Copmanthorpe]]''\n* [[Dalton, Hambleton|Dalton (Hambleton)]], [[Dalton, Richmondshire|Dalton (Richmondshire)]], [[Danby Wiske]], [[Drax, North Yorkshire|Drax]], ''[[Dunnington]]'' \n* [[Easby, Hambleton|Easby]], [[Easingwold]], [[Egton]], ''[[Elvington, City of York|Elvington]]'', ''[[Eston]]'', [[Ebberston]]\n* [[Filey]], [[Folkton]], [[Flixton, North Yorkshire|Flixton]]\n* [[Giggleswick]], [[Glasshouses]], [[Goathland]], ''[[Grangetown, North Yorkshire|Grangetown]]'', [[Grassington]], [[Great Ayton]], [[Grosmont, North Yorkshire|Grosmont]], ''[[Guisborough]]'', [[Ganton, North Yorkshire|Ganton]], [[Glaisdale]]\n* [[Harrogate]], [[Hawes]], ''[[Haxby]]'', [[Hebden, North Yorkshire|Hebden]], [[Helmsley]], [[High Bentham]], [[Horton in Ribblesdale]], [[Hunmanby]], ''[[Huntington, City of York|Huntington]]'', [[Hutton Rudby]]\n* [[Ingleton, North Yorkshire|Ingleton]], ''[[Ingleby Barwick]]''\n* [[Kettlewell]], [[Kilnsey]], [[Kirkbymoorside]], [[Knaresborough]]\n* [[Leyburn]]\n* [[Malham]], [[Malton, North Yorkshire|Malton]], [[Masham]], ''[[Marske-by-the-Sea]]'', [[Middleham]], ''[[Middlesbrough]]'', [[Middleton, Ryedale]], [[Muston, North Yorkshire|Muston]]\n* ''[[New Marske]]'', ''[[Normanby, Redcar and Cleveland|Normanby]]'', [[Northallerton]], [[Norton-on-Derwent]], [[North Grimston]],\n* [[Osmotherley, North Yorkshire|Osmotherley]], ''[[Ormesby]]''\n* [[Pateley Bridge]], [[Pickering, North Yorkshire|Pickering]]\n* '' [[Raskelf]], [[Redcar]]'', [[Reeth]], [[Riccall]], [[Richmond, North Yorkshire|Richmond]], [[Rievaulx]], [[Ripon]], [[Robin Hood's Bay]], [[Romanby]]\n* ''[[Saltburn-by-the-Sea|Saltburn]]'', [[Scagglethorpe]], [[Scampston]], [[Scarborough, North Yorkshire|Scarborough]], [[Scorton, North Yorkshire|Scorton]], [[Selby]], [[Settle, North Yorkshire|Settle]], [[Sherburn-in-Elmet]], [[Sheriff Hutton]], [[Shipton by Beningbrough]], [[Skelton, North Yorkshire|Skelton]], [[Skinningrove]], [[Skipton]], ''[[South Bank, Middlesbrough|South Bank]]'', [[Sowerby, North Yorkshire|Sowerby]], [[Stillington, North Yorkshire|Stillington]], [[Stokesley]], [[Streetlam]], [[Sutton-under-Whitestonecliffe]], [[Swinton, Ryedale|Swinton (near Malton)]]\n* [[Tadcaster]], ''[[Teesville]]'', [[Thirsk]], ''[[Thornaby-on-Tees]]''\n* ''[[Whale Hill]]'', ''[[Wheldrake]]'', [[Whitby]], [[Westow]], [[Wintringham]]\n* ''[[Yarm]]'', ''[[York]]'', [[Yedingham]]\n\n==Places of interest==\n{{EngPlacesKey|align=right}}\n[[Image:Bolton Abbey 7.jpg|thumb|[[Bolton Abbey]]]]\n[[File:Knaresborough Viaduct from River Nidd.jpg|thumb|[[Knaresborough]]]]\n[[Image:Dob Park Lodge.jpg|thumb|An ancient derelict hunting lodge in Dob Park, North Yorkshire.]]\n''Places of interest in italics lie only within the ceremonial county, not the administrative county..''\n\n* [[Ampleforth College]]\n* [[Beningbrough Hall]] \u2013 [[File:NTE icon.svg]] [[File:HH icon.svg]]\n* [[Bolton Abbey]]\n* [[Bolton Castle]] \u2013 [[File:CL icon.svg]] \n* [[Brimham Rocks]] \u2013 [[File:NTE icon.svg]] \n* [[Byland Abbey]] \u2013 [[File:EH icon.svg]] \n* [[Castle Howard]] and the [[Howardian Hills]] \u2013 [[File:HH icon.svg]]\n* [[Catterick Garrison]]\n* [[Cleveland Hills]]\n* [[Drax, North Yorkshire|Drax]]\n* [[Duncombe Park]] \u2013 [[stately home]] [[File:HH icon.svg]]\n* [[Eden Camp Museum]] \u2013 [[File:Museum icon (red).svg]] \n* [[Embsay & Bolton Abbey Steam Railway]] \u2013 [[File:HR icon.svg]] \n* [[Eston Nab]]\n* [[Flamingo Land Theme Park and Zoo]] \u2013 [[File:Zoo icon.jpg|20px]] [[File:Themepark uk icon.png|15px]]\n* [[Fountains Abbey]] \u2013 [[File:NTE icon.svg]] \n* ''[[Gisborough Priory]]''\n* [[Helmsley Castle]] \u2013 [[File:EH icon.svg]] [[File:CL icon.svg]]\n* [[Ingleborough Cave]] \u2013 show cave\n* [[Kirkham Priory]]\n* [[Lightwater Valley]] \u2013 [[File:Themepark uk icon.png|15px]]\n* [[Lund's Tower|Lund\u2019s Tower]]\n* [[Malham Cove]]\n* [[Middleham Castle]] \u2013 [[File:EH icon.svg]] [[File:CL icon.svg]]\n* [[Mount Grace Priory]] \u2013 [[File:EH icon.svg]] \n* [[North Yorkshire Moors Railway]] \u2013 [[File:HR icon.svg]] \n* ''[[Ormesby Hall]]'' \u2013 Palladian Mansion [[File:NTE icon.svg]] [[File:HH icon.svg]] \n* [[Richmond Castle]] \u2013 [[File:CL icon.svg]] \n* [[Rievaulx Abbey]] \u2013 [[File:EH icon.svg]] \n* [[Ripley Castle]] \u2013 Stately home and historic village [[File:HH icon.svg]]\n* [[Ripon Cathedral]] \u2013 [[File:AP Icon.svg]] \n* [[Selby Abbey]]\n* [[Scarborough Castle]] \u2013 [[File:EH icon.svg]] [[File:CL icon.svg]]\n* [[Shandy Hall]] \u2013 stately home [[File:HH icon.svg]]\n* [[Skipton Castle]] \u2013 [[File:CL icon.svg]] \n* [[Stanwick Iron Age Fortifications]] \u2013 [[File:EH icon.svg]] \n* [[Studley Royal Park]] \u2013 [[File:NTE icon.svg]]\n* [[Stump Cross Caverns]] \u2013 show cave\n* ''[[Tees Transporter Bridge]]''\n* [[Thornborough Henges]]\n* [[Earl Crag#Wainman\u2019s Pinnacle|Wainman\u2019s Pinnacle]]\n* [[Wharram Percy]]\n* [[Whitby Abbey]] \u2013 [[File:EH icon.svg]] \n* ''[[York Minster]]'' \u2013 [[File:AP Icon.svg]] \n* ''[[Yorkshire Air Museum]]'' \u2013 [[File:Museum icon (red).svg]]\n* [[The Yorkshire Arboretum]]\n\n==News and media==\nThe County is served by [[BBC North East and Cumbria]], and for more southerly parts of the county [[BBC Yorkshire]]. [[Yorkshire Television]] and [[Tyne Tees Television]] are also received in most areas of the County, [[Settle, North Yorkshire|Settle]] and the Western part of the [[Craven]] area is served by [[BBC North West]] and [[Granada Television]].\n[[BBC Tees]] is broadcast to northern parts of the county, whist [[BBC Radio York]] is broadcast more widely. [[BBC Radio Leeds]] and [[Minster FM]] (Based in [[York]]) broadcast to southern parts of the county.\n\n[[Yorkshire Coast Radio]] serves the coastal towns of Scarborough, Whitby, and Filey providing a daily local news service from studios in Scarborough.\n\n==Transport==\nThe main road through the county is the north\u2013south [[A1(M) motorway (Great Britain)|A1(M)]] which has gradually been upgraded to motorway status since the early 1990s. The only other motorways within the county are the short [[A66 road#A66(M)|A66(M)]] near [[Darlington]] and a small stretch of the [[M62 motorway]] close to [[Eggborough]].<ref name=NY/> The other nationally maintained trunk routes are the [[A168 road|A168]]/[[A19 road|A19]], [[A64 road|A64]], the [[A66 road|A66]] and [[A174 road|A174]].\n\nThe [[East Coast Main Line]] (ECML) bisects the county stopping at [[Northallerton railway station|Northallerton]], [[Thirsk railway station|Thirsk]] and [[York railway station|York]]. Passenger services on the ECML within the county are operated by [[London North Eastern Railway]], [[TransPennine Express]] and [[Grand Central (train operating company)|Grand Central]]. TransPennine Express run services on the [[York to Scarborough Line]] and the [[Northallerton\u2013Eaglescliffe Line]] (for [[Middlesbrough railway station|Middlesbrough]]) that both branch off the ECML.\n\n[[Northern (train operating company)|Northern]] operate the remaining lines in the county including commuter services on the [[Harrogate Line]], [[Airedale Line]] and York & Selby Lines, of which the former two are covered by the [[West Yorkshire Metro|Metro]] ticketing area. Remaining branch lines operated by Northern include the [[Yorkshire Coast Line]] from Scarborough to Hull, the [[Hull to York Line]] via [[Selby railway station|Selby]], the [[Tees Valley Line]] from [[Darlington railway station|Darlington]] to [[Saltburn railway station|Saltburn]] and the [[Esk Valley Line]] from Middlesbrough to [[Whitby railway station|Whitby]]. Last but certainly not least, the [[Settle-Carlisle Line]] runs through the west of the county with services again operated by Northern.\n[[File:North yorkshire moors railway map.gif|thumb|right|Current and former railway routes in eastern North Yorkshire]]\nThe county suffered badly under the [[Beeching Axe|Beeching]] cuts of the 1960s. Places such as [[Richmond railway station (North Yorkshire)|Richmond]], [[Ripon railway station|Ripon]], [[Tadcaster railway station|Tadcaster]], [[Helmsley railway station|Helmsley]], [[Pickering railway station|Pickering]] and the [[Wensleydale]] communities lost their passenger services. Notable lines closed were the [[Scarborough and Whitby Railway]], [[Malton and Driffield Railway]] and the secondary main line between Northallerton and Harrogate via Ripon.\n\nHeritage railways within North Yorkshire include the [[North Yorkshire Moors Railway]] between [[Pickering, North Yorkshire|Pickering]] and [[Grosmont, North Yorkshire|Grosmont]], which opened in 1973, the [[Derwent Valley Light Railway]] near York, and the [[Embsay and Bolton Abbey Steam Railway]]. The [[Wensleydale Railway]], which started operating in 2003, runs services between [[Leeming Bar railway station|Leeming Bar]] and [[Redmire railway station|Redmire]] along a former freight-only line. The medium-term aim is to operate into Northallerton station on the ECML once an agreement can be reached with [[Network Rail]]. In the longer term, the aim is to reinstate the full line west via [[Hawes]] to [[Garsdale railway station|Garsdale]] on the Settle-Carlisle line.\n\n[[York railway station]] is the largest station in the county with 11 platforms and is a major tourist attraction in its own right. The station is immediately adjacent to the [[National Railway Museum]].\n\nLong-distance coach services are operated by [[National Express Coaches|National Express]] and [[Megabus (Europe)|Megabus]]. Local bus service operators include [[Arriva Yorkshire]], [[Harrogate Bus Company]], Scarborough & District ([[East Yorkshire Motor Services]]), [[Yorkshire Coastliner]], [[First York]] and the local [[Dales & District]].\n\nThere are no major airports in the county itself but nearby airports include [[Durham Tees Valley Airport|Durham Tees Valley]], [[Newcastle International Airport|Newcastle]], [[Robin Hood Airport Doncaster Sheffield|Robin Hood Doncaster Sheffield]] and [[Leeds Bradford International Airport|Leeds Bradford]].\n\n==Sports==\nNorth Yorkshire is home to several football clubs, including [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] who play in the [[EFL Championship|Championship]] and [[Harrogate Town F.C.|Harrogate Town]] who play in the [[National League (division)|National League]] finishing in 6th place and qualifying for the National League playoffs in their first season in the league. [[York City F.C.|York City]] who play in The [[National League North]] and finished 11th during the [[2017-18 National League]] season. [[Whitby Town FC]] have reached the FA Cup first round seven times, and have played the likes of [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]], Wigan and Plymouth Argyle, they currently play in the Evo-Stik Premier League. Other lower league clubs include [[Harrogate Railway Athletic F.C.|Harrogate Railway Athletic]], [[Northallerton Town F.C.|Northallerton Town]], [[Pickering Town F.C.|Pickering Town]], [[Scarborough Athletic F.C.|Scarborough Athletic]], [[Selby Town F.C.|Selby Town]] and [[Tadcaster Albion F.C.|Tadcaster Albion]].\n\n[[Rugby union]] teams in the county include [[Middlesbrough rugby union football team|Middlesbrough RUFC]] who play their league games in [[Durham/Northumberland 1]]. [[York City Knights]] (previously [[York F.C.]]) are a [[rugby league]] team who play in the [[Rugby League Championships]].\n\nNorth Yorkshire is home to many [[racecourses]]; these include [[Catterick Bridge Racecourse|Catterick Bridge]], [[Redcar Racecourse|Redcar]], [[Ripon Racecourse|Ripon]], [[Thirsk Racecourse|Thirsk]] and [[York Racecourse|York]]. It also has one [[Auto racing|motor racing]] circuit, [[Croft Circuit]]; the circuit holds meetings of the [[British Touring Car Championship]], [[British Superbike]] and [[Pickup Truck Racing]] race series and one Motorcycle Racing Circuit at Oliver's Mount, Scarborough.\n\n[[Yorkshire County Cricket Club]], play a number of fixtures at [[North Marine Road]], [[Scarborough, North Yorkshire|Scarborough]].\n\nThe ball game [[Rock-It-Ball]] was developed in the county.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Lord Lieutenant of North Yorkshire|List of Lords Lieutenant of North Yorkshire]]\n* [[High Sheriff of North Yorkshire|List of High Sheriffs of North Yorkshire]]\n* [[North Yorkshire Police]]\n* [[North Yorkshire Police and Crime Commissioner]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=Notes}}\n\